China  needs to keep monetary policy
tight as the risk of inflation still exists, International
Monetary Fund Deputy Managing Director Zhu Min said at the  World
Economic Forum  in the northeastern Chinese city of Dalian.  Inflation will be a long-term phenomenon, Zhu said.  China needs to closely monitor the market and economy as
the global economy slows down, Zhu said. China needs to balance
growth and inflation, Zhu said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
